Elapsed: 00:00:00.05
08:25:11 SQL> 
08:25:11 SQL> --------------------------------
08:25:11 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:25:11 SQL> --
08:25:11 SQL> 
08:25:11 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:25:11 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:25:11 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:25:11 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:25:11 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:25:11 SQL> 
08:25:11 SQL> BEGIN
08:25:11   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:25:11   3  	-- create miss tables
08:25:11   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:25:11   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:25:11   6  
08:25:11   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:25:11   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:25:11   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:25:11  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:11  12  
08:25:11  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:25:11  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:25:11  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:11  17  
08:25:11  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:25:11  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:25:11  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:25:11  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:25:11  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:25:11  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:25:11  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:25:11  27  
08:25:11  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:25:11  29  	-- create clip table
08:25:11  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:25:11  31  
08:25:11  32  	-- populate clip table
08:25:11  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:25:11  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:25:11  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:25:11  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:11  38  
08:25:11  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:25:11  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:25:11  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:25:11  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:25:11  44  
08:25:11  45  	-- create normalization table
08:25:11  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:25:11  47  
08:25:11  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:25:11  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:25:11  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:25:11  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:25:11  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:11  53  
08:25:11  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:25:11  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:25:11  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:25:11  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:11  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:25:11  59  END;
08:25:11  60  /
old  10:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'bme',

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:25:55 SQL> -----------------------
08:25:55 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:25:55 SQL> --
08:25:55 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:25:55 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:25:55 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:25:55 SQL> --
08:25:55 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:25:55 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:25:55 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:25:55 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:25:55 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:25:55 SQL> --
08:25:55 SQL> BEGIN
08:25:55   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:25:55   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:25:55   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:25:55   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:25:55   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:25:55   7  
08:25:55   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:25:55   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:25:55  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:25:55  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:25:55  12  
08:25:55  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:25:55  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:25:55  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:25:55  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:25:55  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:25:55  18  END;
08:25:55  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

08:25:57 SQL> @score.sql
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> -- score.sql
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:25:57 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:25:57 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:25:57 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:25:57 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:25:57 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_cat;

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:25:57 SQL> DELETE svmc_clip;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:25:57 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:25:57 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:25:57 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:25:57 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:25:57 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:25:57 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:25:57 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:25:57 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:25:57 SQL> -- models.
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:25:57 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:25:57 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:25:57 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:25:57 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:25:57 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:25:57 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:25:57 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:25:57 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:25:57 SQL> -- END;
08:25:57 SQL> -- /
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------

SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> --------------------------------
08:25:57 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:25:57 SQL> --
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:25:57 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:25:57 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:25:57 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:25:57 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:25:57 SQL> 
08:25:57 SQL> BEGIN
08:25:57   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:25:57   3  	-- create miss tables
08:25:57   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:25:57   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:25:57   6  
08:25:57   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:25:57   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:25:57   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:25:57  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:57  12  
08:25:57  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:25:57  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:25:57  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:57  17  
08:25:57  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:25:57  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:25:57  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:25:57  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:25:57  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:25:57  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:25:57  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:25:57  27  
08:25:57  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:25:57  29  	-- create clip table
08:25:57  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:25:57  31  
08:25:57  32  	-- populate clip table
08:25:57  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:25:57  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:25:57  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:25:57  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:57  38  
08:25:57  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:25:57  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:25:57  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:25:57  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:25:57  44  
08:25:57  45  	-- create normalization table
08:25:57  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:25:57  47  
08:25:57  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:25:57  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:25:57  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:25:57  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:25:57  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:25:57  53  
08:25:57  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:25:57  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:25:57  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:25:57  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:25:57  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:25:57  59  END;

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.07
08:26:51 SQL> -----------------------
08:26:51 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:26:51 SQL> --
08:26:51 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:26:51 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:26:51 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:26:51 SQL> --
08:26:51 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:26:51 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:26:51 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:26:51 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:26:51 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:26:51 SQL> --
08:26:51 SQL> BEGIN
08:26:51   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:26:51   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:26:51   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:26:51   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:26:51   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:26:51   7  
08:26:51   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:26:51   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:26:51  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:26:51  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:26:51  12  
08:26:51  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:26:51  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:26:51  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:26:51  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:26:51  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:26:51  18  END;
08:26:51  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Now build model from bme and score sme
08:26:53 SQL> @score1.sql
08:26:53 SQL> -- score1.sql
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Does the 1st SVM score
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Fill up svmc_apply_prep
08:26:53 SQL> @score.sql
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> -- score.sql
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:26:53 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:26:53 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:26:53 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:26:53 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:26:53 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_cat;

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:26:53 SQL> DELETE svmc_clip;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:26:53 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:26:53 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:26:53 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:26:53 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:26:53 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:26:53 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:26:53 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:26:53 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:26:53 SQL> -- models.
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:26:53 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:26:53 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:26:53 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:26:53 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:26:53 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:26:53 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:26:53 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:26:53 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:26:53 SQL> -- END;
08:26:53 SQL> -- /
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------
ALGO_NAME		       ALGO_SUPPORT_VECTOR_MACHINES
SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> BEGIN EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'DROP VIEW xformed_build_miss_cat';
08:26:53   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;
08:26:53   3  /

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> --------------------------------
08:26:53 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:26:53 SQL> --
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:26:53 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:26:53 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:26:53 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:26:53 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:26:53 SQL> 
08:26:53 SQL> BEGIN
08:26:53   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:26:53   3  	-- create miss tables
08:26:53   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:26:53   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:26:53   6  
08:26:53   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:26:53   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:26:53   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:26:53  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:26:53  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:26:53  12  
08:26:53  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:26:53  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:26:53  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:26:53  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:26:53  17  
08:26:53  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:26:53  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:26:53  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',

08:27:40 SQL> -----------------------
08:27:40 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:27:40 SQL> --
08:27:40 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:27:40 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:27:40 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:27:40 SQL> --
08:27:40 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:27:40 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:27:40 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:27:40 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:27:40 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:27:40 SQL> --
08:27:40 SQL> BEGIN
08:27:40   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:27:40   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:27:40   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:27:40   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:27:40   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:27:40   7  
08:27:40   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:27:40   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:27:40  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:27:40  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:27:40  12  
08:27:40  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:27:40  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:27:40  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:27:40  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:27:40  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:27:40  18  END;

08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:27:42 SQL>

08:27:42 SQL>

08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:27:42 SQL> --
08:27:42 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:27:42 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:27:42 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:27:42 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:27:42 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:27:42 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:27:42 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:27:42 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:27:42 SQL> -- models.
08:27:42 SQL> --
08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:27:42 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:27:42 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:27:42 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:27:42 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:27:42 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:27:42 SQL> --
08:27:42 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:27:42 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:27:42 SQL> --
08:27:42 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:27:42 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:27:42 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:27:42 SQL> -- END;
08:27:42 SQL> -- /
08:27:42 SQL> 
08:27:42 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

------------------------------ ------------------------------

08:27:43   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.05
08:27:43 SQL> 
08:27:43 SQL> --------------------------------
08:27:43 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:27:43 SQL> --
08:27:43 SQL> 
08:27:43 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:27:43 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:27:43 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:27:43 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:27:43 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:27:43 SQL> 
08:27:43 SQL> BEGIN
08:27:43   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:27:43   3  	-- create miss tables
08:27:43   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:27:43   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:27:43   6  
08:27:43   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:27:43   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:27:43   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:27:43  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:27:43  12  
08:27:43  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:27:43  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:27:43  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:27:43  17  
08:27:43  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:27:43  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:27:43  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:27:43  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:27:43  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:27:43  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:27:43  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:27:43  27  
08:27:43  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:27:43  29  	-- create clip table
08:27:43  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:27:43  31  
08:27:43  32  	-- populate clip table
08:27:43  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:27:43  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:27:43  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:27:43  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:27:43  38  
08:27:43  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:27:43  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:27:43  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:27:43  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:27:43  44  
08:27:43  45  	-- create normalization table
08:27:43  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:27:43  47  
08:27:43  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:27:43  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:27:43  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:27:43  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:27:43  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:27:43  53  
08:27:43  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:27:43  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:27:43  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:27:43  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:27:43  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:27:43  59  END;
08:27:43  60  /
old  10:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'bme',
old  11:     exclude_list    => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:28:29 SQL> -----------------------
08:28:29 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:28:29 SQL> --
08:28:29 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:28:29 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:28:29 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:28:29 SQL> --
08:28:29 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:28:29 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:28:29 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:28:29 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:28:29 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:28:29 SQL> --
08:28:29 SQL> BEGIN
08:28:29   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:28:29   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:28:29   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:28:29   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:28:29   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:28:29   7  
08:28:29   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:28:29   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:28:29  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:28:29  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:28:29  12  
08:28:29  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:28:29  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:28:29  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:28:29  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:28:29  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:28:29  18  END;
08:28:29  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

08:28:30 SQL>

08:28:30 SQL> 
08:28:30 SQL> 
08:28:30 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:28:30 SQL> --
08:28:30 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:28:30 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:28:30 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:28:30 SQL> 
08:28:30 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:28:30 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:28:30 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:28:30 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:28:30 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:28:30 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:28:30 SQL> -- models.
08:28:30 SQL> --
08:28:30 SQL> 
08:28:30 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:28:30 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:28:30 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:28:30 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:28:30 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:28:30 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:28:30 SQL> --
08:28:30 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:28:30 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:28:30 SQL> --
08:28:30 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:28:30 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:28:30 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:28:30 SQL> -- END;
08:28:30 SQL> -- /
08:28:30 SQL> 
08:28:30 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------

SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

08:28:31 SQL> 
08:28:31 SQL> --------------------------------
08:28:31 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:28:31 SQL> --
08:28:31 SQL> 
08:28:31 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:28:31 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:28:31 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:28:31 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:28:31 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:28:31 SQL> 
08:28:31 SQL> BEGIN
08:28:31   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:28:31   3  	-- create miss tables
08:28:31   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:28:31   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:28:31   6  
08:28:31   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:28:31   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:28:31   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:28:31  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:28:31  12  
08:28:31  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:28:31  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:28:31  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:28:31  17  
08:28:31  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:28:31  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:28:31  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:28:31  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:28:31  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:28:31  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:28:31  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:28:31  27  
08:28:31  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:28:31  29  	-- create clip table
08:28:31  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:28:31  31  
08:28:31  32  	-- populate clip table
08:28:31  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:28:31  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:28:31  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:28:31  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:28:31  38  
08:28:31  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:28:31  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:28:31  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:28:31  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:28:31  44  
08:28:31  45  	-- create normalization table
08:28:31  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:28:31  47  
08:28:31  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:28:31  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:28:31  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:28:31  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:28:31  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:28:31  53  
08:28:31  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:28:31  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:28:31  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:28:31  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:28:31  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:28:31  59  END;
08:28:31  60  /

08:29:17 SQL> -----------------------
08:29:17 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:29:17 SQL> --
08:29:17 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:29:17 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:29:17 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:29:17 SQL> --
08:29:17 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:29:17 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:29:17 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:29:17 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:29:17 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:29:17 SQL> --
08:29:17 SQL> BEGIN
08:29:17   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:29:17   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:29:17   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:29:17   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:29:17   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:29:17   7  
08:29:17   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:29:17   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:29:17  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:29:17  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:29:17  12  
08:29:17  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:29:17  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:29:17  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:29:17  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:29:17  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:29:17  18  END;
08:29:17  19  /

old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Now build model from bme and score sme
08:29:18 SQL> @score1.sql
08:29:18 SQL> -- score1.sql
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Does the 1st SVM score
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Fill up svmc_apply_prep
08:29:18 SQL> @score.sql
08:29:18 SQL> --
08:29:18 SQL> -- score.sql
08:29:18 SQL> --
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:29:18 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:29:18 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:29:18 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:29:18 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:29:18 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_cat;

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:29:18 SQL> DELETE svmc_clip;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:29:18 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:29:18 SQL> --
08:29:18 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:29:18 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:29:18 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:29:18 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:29:18 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:29:18 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:29:18 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:29:18 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:29:18 SQL> -- models.
08:29:18 SQL> --
08:29:18 SQL> 
08:29:18 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:29:19 SQL> 
08:29:19 SQL> --------------------------------
08:29:19 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:29:19 SQL> --
08:29:19 SQL> 
08:29:19 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:29:19 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:29:19 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:29:19 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:29:19 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:29:19 SQL> 
08:29:19 SQL> BEGIN
08:29:19   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:29:19   3  	-- create miss tables
08:29:19   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:29:19   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:29:19   6  
08:29:19   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:29:19   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:29:19   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:29:19  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:29:19  12  
08:29:19  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:29:19  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:29:19  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:29:19  17  
08:29:19  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:29:19  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:29:19  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:29:19  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:29:19  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:29:19  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:29:19  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:29:19  27  
08:29:19  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:29:19  29  	-- create clip table
08:29:19  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:29:19  31  
08:29:19  32  	-- populate clip table
08:29:19  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:29:19  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:29:19  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:29:19  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:29:19  38  
08:29:19  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:29:19  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:29:19  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:29:19  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:29:19  44  
08:29:19  45  	-- create normalization table
08:29:19  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:29:19  47  
08:29:19  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:29:19  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:29:19  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:29:19  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:29:19  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:29:19  53  
08:29:19  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:29:19  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:29:19  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:29:19  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:29:19  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:29:19  59  END;
08:29:19  60  /

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:05 SQL> -----------------------
08:30:05 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:30:05 SQL> --
08:30:05 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:30:05 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:30:05 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:30:05 SQL> --
08:30:05 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:30:05 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:30:05 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:30:05 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:30:05 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:30:05 SQL> --
08:30:05 SQL> BEGIN
08:30:05   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:30:05   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:30:05   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:05   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:05   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:30:05   7  
08:30:05   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:30:05   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:05  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:05  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:30:05  12  
08:30:05  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:30:05  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:30:05  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:30:05  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:05  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:30:05  18  END;
08:30:05  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Now build model from bme and score sme
08:30:07 SQL> @score1.sql
08:30:07 SQL> -- score1.sql
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Does the 1st SVM score
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Fill up svmc_apply_prep
08:30:07 SQL> @score.sql
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> -- score.sql
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:30:07 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:30:07 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:30:07 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:30:07 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:30:07 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_cat;

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:30:07 SQL> DELETE svmc_clip;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:30:07 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:30:07 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:30:07 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:30:07 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:30:07 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:30:07 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:30:07 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:30:07 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:30:07 SQL> -- models.
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:30:07 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:30:07 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:30:07 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:30:07 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:07 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:07 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:07 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:30:07 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:30:07 SQL> -- END;
08:30:07 SQL> -- /
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------
ALGO_NAME		       ALGO_SUPPORT_VECTOR_MACHINES
SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00

08:30:07   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;
08:30:07   3  /

Elapsed: 00:00:00.05
08:30:07 SQL> BEGIN EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'DROP VIEW svmc_build_prep';
08:30:07   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:07 SQL> BEGIN EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'DROP VIEW xformed_build_miss_num';
08:30:07   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;
08:30:07   3  /

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> BEGIN EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'DROP VIEW xformed_build_miss_cat';
08:30:07   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;
08:30:07   3  /

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> --------------------------------
08:30:07 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:30:07 SQL> --
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:30:07 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:30:07 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:30:07 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:30:07 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:30:07 SQL> 
08:30:07 SQL> BEGIN
08:30:07   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:30:07   3  	-- create miss tables
08:30:07   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:30:07   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:30:07   6  
08:30:07   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:30:07   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:30:07   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:07  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:07  12  
08:30:07  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:30:07  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:07  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:07  17  
08:30:07  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:30:07  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:30:07  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:07  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:30:07  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:30:07  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:07  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:30:07  27  
08:30:07  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:30:07  29  	-- create clip table
08:30:07  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:30:07  31  
08:30:07  32  	-- populate clip table
08:30:07  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:30:07  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:30:07  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:30:07  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:07  38  
08:30:07  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:30:07  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:30:07  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:30:07  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:07  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:30:07  44  
08:30:07  45  	-- create normalization table
08:30:07  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:30:07  47  
08:30:07  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:30:07  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:30:07  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:30:07  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:30:07  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:07  53  
08:30:07  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:30:07  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:53 SQL> -----------------------
08:30:53 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:30:53 SQL> --
08:30:53 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:30:53 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:30:53 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:30:53 SQL> --
08:30:53 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:30:53 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:30:53 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:30:53 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:30:53 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:30:53 SQL> --
08:30:53 SQL> BEGIN
08:30:53   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:30:53   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:30:53   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:53   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:53   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:30:53   7  
08:30:53   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:30:53   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:53  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:53  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:30:53  12  
08:30:53  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:30:53  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:30:53  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:30:53  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:30:53  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:30:53  18  END;
08:30:53  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

08:30:54 SQL> --
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:30:54 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'

08:30:54 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:30:54 SQL>

08:30:54 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:30:54 SQL>

08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:30:54 SQL> --
08:30:54 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:30:54 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:30:54 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:30:54 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:30:54 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:30:54 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:30:54 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:30:54 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:30:54 SQL> -- models.
08:30:54 SQL> --
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:30:54 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:30:54 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:30:54 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:30:54 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:54 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:30:54 SQL> --
08:30:54 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:54 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:30:54 SQL> --
08:30:54 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:30:54 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:30:54 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:30:54 SQL> -- END;
08:30:54 SQL> -- /
08:30:54 SQL> 
08:30:54 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------

SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:30:55 SQL> 
08:30:55 SQL> --------------------------------
08:30:55 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:30:55 SQL> --
08:30:55 SQL> 
08:30:55 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:30:55 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:30:55 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:30:55 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:30:55 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:30:55 SQL> 
08:30:55 SQL> BEGIN
08:30:55   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:30:55   3  	-- create miss tables
08:30:55   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:30:55   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:30:55   6  
08:30:55   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:30:55   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:30:55   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:55  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:55  12  
08:30:55  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:30:55  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:55  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:55  17  
08:30:55  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:30:55  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:30:55  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:30:55  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:30:55  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:30:55  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:30:55  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:30:55  27  
08:30:55  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:30:55  29  	-- create clip table
08:30:55  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:30:55  31  
08:30:55  32  	-- populate clip table
08:30:55  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:30:55  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:30:55  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:30:55  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:55  38  
08:30:55  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:30:55  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:30:55  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:30:55  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:30:55  44  
08:30:55  45  	-- create normalization table
08:30:55  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:30:55  47  
08:30:55  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:30:55  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:30:55  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:30:55  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:30:55  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:30:55  53  
08:30:55  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:30:55  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:30:55  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:30:55  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:30:55  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:30:55  59  END;
08:30:55  60  /
old  10:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'bme',
old  11:     exclude_list    => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
new  11:     exclude_list    => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST ('gatt','prdate'));

08:31:47 SQL> BEGIN EXECUTE IMMEDIATE 'DROP VIEW svmc_apply_prep';

08:31:47   3  /

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:31:47 SQL> -----------------------
08:31:47 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:31:47 SQL> --
08:31:47 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:31:47 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:31:47 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:31:47 SQL> --
08:31:47 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:31:47 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:31:47 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:31:47 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:31:47 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:31:47 SQL> --
08:31:47 SQL> BEGIN
08:31:47   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:31:47   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:31:47   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:31:47   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:31:47   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:31:47   7  
08:31:47   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:31:47   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:31:47  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:31:47  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:31:47  12  
08:31:47  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:31:47  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:31:47  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:31:47  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:31:47  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:31:47  18  END;
08:31:47  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',

08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:31:49 SQL> --
08:31:49 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:31:49 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:31:49 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:31:49 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:31:49 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:31:49 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:31:49 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:31:49 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:31:49 SQL> -- models.
08:31:49 SQL> --
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:31:49 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:31:49 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:31:49 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:31:49 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:31:49 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:31:49 SQL> --
08:31:49 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:31:49 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:31:49 SQL> --
08:31:49 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:31:49 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:31:49 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:31:49 SQL> -- END;
08:31:49 SQL> -- /
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------

SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

Elapsed: 00:00:00.07
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> --------------------------------
08:31:49 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:31:49 SQL> --
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:31:49 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:31:49 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:31:49 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:31:49 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:31:49 SQL> 
08:31:49 SQL> BEGIN
08:31:49   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:31:49   3  	-- create miss tables
08:31:49   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:31:49   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:31:49   6  
08:31:49   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:31:49   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:31:49   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:31:49  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:31:49  12  
08:31:49  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:31:49  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:31:49  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:31:49  17  
08:31:49  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:31:49  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:31:49  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:31:49  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:31:49  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:31:49  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:31:49  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:31:49  27  
08:31:49  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:31:49  29  	-- create clip table
08:31:49  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:31:49  31  
08:31:49  32  	-- populate clip table
08:31:49  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:31:49  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:31:49  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:31:49  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:31:49  38  
08:31:49  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:31:49  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:31:49  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:31:49  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:31:49  44  
08:31:49  45  	-- create normalization table
08:31:49  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:31:49  47  
08:31:49  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:31:49  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:31:49  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:31:49  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:31:49  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:31:49  53  
08:31:49  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:31:49  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:31:49  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:31:49  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:31:49  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:31:49  59  END;
08:31:49  60  /
old  10:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'bme',

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:32:34 SQL> -----------------------
08:32:34 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:32:34 SQL> --
08:32:34 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:32:34 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:32:34 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:32:34 SQL> --
08:32:34 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:32:34 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:32:34 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:32:34 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:32:34 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:32:34 SQL> --
08:32:34 SQL> BEGIN
08:32:34   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:32:34   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:32:34   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:32:34   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:32:34   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:32:34   7  
08:32:34   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:32:34   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:32:34  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:32:34  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:32:34  12  
08:32:34  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:32:34  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:32:34  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:32:34  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:32:34  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:32:34  18  END;
08:32:34  19  /

new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',

new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

08:32:36 SQL> -- Now build model from bme and score sme
08:32:36 SQL> @score1.sql
08:32:36 SQL> -- score1.sql
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Does the 1st SVM score
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Fill up svmc_apply_prep
08:32:36 SQL> @score.sql
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> -- score.sql
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:32:36 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:32:36 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:32:36 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:32:36 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:32:36 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_cat;

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:32:36 SQL> DELETE svmc_clip;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:32:36 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:32:36 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:32:36 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:32:36 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:32:36 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:32:36 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:32:36 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:32:36 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:32:36 SQL> -- models.
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:32:36 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:32:36 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:32:36 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:32:36 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:32:36 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:32:36 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:32:36 SQL> --
08:32:36 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:32:36 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:32:36 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:32:36 SQL> -- END;
08:32:36 SQL> -- /
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

SETTING_NAME		       SETTING_VALUE
------------------------------ ------------------------------
ALGO_NAME		       ALGO_SUPPORT_VECTOR_MACHINES
SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123

08:32:36 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:32:36 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:32:36 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:32:36 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:32:36 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:32:36 SQL> 
08:32:36 SQL> BEGIN
08:32:36   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:32:36   3  	-- create miss tables
08:32:36   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:32:36   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:32:36   6  
08:32:36   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:32:36   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:32:36   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:32:36  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:32:36  12  
08:32:36  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:32:36  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:32:36  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:32:36  17  
08:32:36  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:32:36  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:32:36  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:32:36  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:32:36  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:32:36  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:32:36  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:32:36  27  
08:32:36  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:32:36  29  	-- create clip table
08:32:36  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:32:36  31  
08:32:36  32  	-- populate clip table
08:32:36  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:32:36  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:32:36  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:32:36  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:32:36  38  
08:32:36  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:32:36  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:32:36  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:32:36  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:32:36  44  
08:32:36  45  	-- create normalization table
08:32:36  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:32:36  47  
08:32:36  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:32:36  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:32:36  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:32:36  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:32:36  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:32:36  53  
08:32:36  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:32:36  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:32:36  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:32:36  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:32:36  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:32:36  59  END;
08:32:36  60  /
old  10:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'bme',
old  11:     exclude_list    => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
new  11:     exclude_list    => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST ('gatt','prdate'));
old  15:     data_table_name => '&bldtable',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:33:22 SQL> -----------------------
08:33:22 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:33:22 SQL> --
08:33:22 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:33:22 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:33:22 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:33:22 SQL> --
08:33:22 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:33:22 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:33:22 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:33:22 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:33:22 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:33:22 SQL> --
08:33:22 SQL> BEGIN
08:33:22   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:33:22   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:33:22   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:33:22   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:33:22   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:33:22   7  
08:33:22   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:33:22   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:33:22  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:33:22  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:33:22  12  
08:33:22  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:33:22  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:33:22  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:33:22  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:33:22  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:33:22  18  END;
08:33:22  19  /

08:33:24 SQL> -- Now build model from bme and score sme
08:33:24 SQL> @score1.sql
08:33:24 SQL> -- score1.sql
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Does the 1st SVM score
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Fill up svmc_apply_prep
08:33:24 SQL> @score.sql
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> -- score.sql
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- usage: score.sql
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- A script which feeds data to SVM and captures the results in table svmc_apply_prep
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE target	= 'gatt'
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE model_name = 'forex14'
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE bldtable	= 'bme'
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE scoretable = 'sme'
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE case_id	= 'prdate'
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Define a variable to help me exclude some columns from some data mining calls
08:33:24 SQL> DEFINE exclude1 = "'&target','&case_id'"
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Builds an SVM model using pl/sql.
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:33:24 SQL> --			    BUILD THE MODEL
08:33:24 SQL> -----------------------------------------------------------------------
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Cleanup old build data preparation objects for repeat runs
08:33:24 SQL> DELETE svmc_miss_num;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00

0 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.00
08:33:24 SQL> DELETE svmc_norm;

247 rows deleted.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.01
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- CREATE AND POPULATE A SETTINGS TABLE
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> -- DROP	TABLE svmc_settings ;
08:33:24 SQL> -- CREATE TABLE svmc_settings ( setting_name  VARCHAR2(30), setting_value VARCHAR2(30));
08:33:24 SQL> -- DELETE svmc_settings;
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- The default classification algorithm is Naive Bayes. So override
08:33:24 SQL> -- this choice to SVM using a settings table.
08:33:24 SQL> -- SVM chooses a kernel type automatically. This choice can be overriden
08:33:24 SQL> -- by the user. Linear kernel is preferred high dimensional data, and
08:33:24 SQL> -- Gaussian kernel for low dimensional data. Here we use linear kernel
08:33:24 SQL> -- to demonstrate the get_model_details_svm() API, which applies only for
08:33:24 SQL> -- models.
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> -- Do this once and then comment it out.
08:33:24 SQL> -- That makes script go faster.
08:33:24 SQL> -- BEGIN
08:33:24 SQL> -- -- Populate settings table
08:33:24 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:33:24 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.algo_name, dbms_data_mining.algo_support_vector_machines);
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:33:24 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_function, dbms_data_mining.svms_gaussian);
08:33:24 SQL> --
08:33:24 SQL> --   INSERT INTO svmc_settings (setting_name, setting_value) VALUES
08:33:24 SQL> --   (dbms_data_mining.svms_kernel_cache_size,190123123);
08:33:24 SQL> --   COMMIT;
08:33:24 SQL> -- END;
08:33:24 SQL> -- /
08:33:24 SQL> 
08:33:24 SQL> SELECT * FROM svmc_settings;

------------------------------ ------------------------------

SVMS_KERNEL_FUNCTION	       SVMS_GAUSSIAN
SVMS_KERNEL_CACHE_SIZE	       320123123
