Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:33:25 SQL> 
08:33:25 SQL> --------------------------------
08:33:25 SQL> -- PREPARE BUILD (TRAINING) DATA
08:33:25 SQL> --
08:33:25 SQL> 
08:33:25 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:33:25 SQL> -- 2. Outlier Treatment and
08:33:25 SQL> -- 3. Normalization are performed below.
08:33:25 SQL> --    NOTE: that unlike SVM regression, the classification target is NOT
08:33:25 SQL> --    normalized here.
08:33:25 SQL> 
08:33:25 SQL> BEGIN
08:33:25   2  	-- Perform missing value treatment for all predictors
08:33:25   3  	-- create miss tables
08:33:25   4  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_NUM (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num');
08:33:25   5  	--  DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_MISS_CAT (miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat');
08:33:25   6  
08:33:25   7  	-- populate miss tables
08:33:25   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_NUM_MEAN (
08:33:25   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:33:25  10  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  11  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:33:25  12  
08:33:25  13  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_MISS_CAT_MODE (
08:33:25  14  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:33:25  15  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  16  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:33:25  17  
08:33:25  18  	-- xform input data to replace missing values
08:33:25  19  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:33:25  20  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:33:25  21  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  22  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_num');
08:33:25  23  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:33:25  24  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:33:25  25  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  26  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_build_miss_cat');
08:33:25  27  
08:33:25  28  	-- Perform outlier treatment.
08:33:25  29  	-- create clip table
08:33:25  30  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_CLIP (clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip');
08:33:25  31  
08:33:25  32  	-- populate clip table
08:33:25  33  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_CLIP_WINSOR_TAIL (
08:33:25  34  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:33:25  35  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  36  	  tail_frac	  => 0.025,
08:33:25  37  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:33:25  38  
08:33:25  39  	-- xform input data to winsorized data
08:33:25  40  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_CLIP(
08:33:25  41  	  clip_table_name => 'svmc_clip',
08:33:25  42  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  43  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_winsor');
08:33:25  44  
08:33:25  45  	-- create normalization table
08:33:25  46  	-- DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.CREATE_NORM_LIN (norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm');
08:33:25  47  
08:33:25  48  	-- populate normalization table based on winsorized data
08:33:25  49  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.INSERT_NORM_LIN_MINMAX (
08:33:25  50  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:33:25  51  	  data_table_name => 'svmc_winsor',
08:33:25  52  	  exclude_list	  => DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.COLUMN_LIST (&exclude1));
08:33:25  53  
08:33:25  54  	-- normalize the original data
08:33:25  55  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:33:25  56  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:33:25  57  	  data_table_name => '&bldtable',
08:33:25  58  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_build_prep');
08:33:25  59  END;
08:33:25  60  /

08:34:10   2  EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN NULL; END;
08:34:10   3  /

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.

Elapsed: 00:00:00.06
08:34:10 SQL> -----------------------
08:34:10 SQL> -- PREPARE SCORING DATA
08:34:10 SQL> --
08:34:10 SQL> -- If the data for model creation has been prepared, then the data
08:34:10 SQL> -- to be scored using the model must be prepared in the same manner
08:34:10 SQL> -- in order to obtain meaningful results.
08:34:10 SQL> --
08:34:10 SQL> -- 1. Missing Value treatment for all Predictors and
08:34:10 SQL> -- 2. Normalization
08:34:10 SQL> -- No outlier treatment will be performed during test and apply. The
08:34:10 SQL> -- normalization step is sufficient, since the normalization parameters
08:34:10 SQL> -- already capture the effects of outlier treatment done with build data.
08:34:10 SQL> --
08:34:10 SQL> BEGIN
08:34:10   2  	-- Xform Test data to replace missing values
08:34:10   3  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_NUM(
08:34:10   4  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_num',
08:34:10   5  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:34:10   6  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_num');
08:34:10   7  
08:34:10   8  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_MISS_CAT(
08:34:10   9  	  miss_table_name => 'svmc_miss_cat',
08:34:10  10  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:34:10  11  	  xform_view_name => 'xformed_apply_miss_cat');
08:34:10  12  
08:34:10  13  	-- Normalize the data to be scored
08:34:10  14  	DBMS_DATA_MINING_TRANSFORM.XFORM_NORM_LIN (
08:34:10  15  	  norm_table_name => 'svmc_norm',
08:34:10  16  	  data_table_name => '&scoretable',
08:34:10  17  	  xform_view_name => 'svmc_apply_prep');
08:34:10  18  END;
08:34:10  19  /
old   5:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new   5:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  10:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  10:     data_table_name => 'sme',
old  16:     data_table_name => '&scoretable',
new  16:     data_table_name => 'sme',

PL/SQL procedure successfully completed.
